1
00:00:09,567 --> 00:00:10,667
The rumors are true!

2
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:14,033
I'm running for mayor
of Calabari!

3
00:00:14,167 --> 00:00:15,933
We are in a democracy.

4
00:00:16,067 --> 00:00:19,433
You can run as long as
you're qualified.

5
00:00:21,867 --> 00:00:23,133
I'm letting your godmother
rest for now.

6
00:00:23,267 --> 00:00:24,467
Her early retirement is just
around the corner.

7
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:25,833
It's too dangerous if she joins
the fight again.

8
00:00:25,967 --> 00:00:27,867
I took two pregnancy tests.

9
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,167
- Both came out positive!
- Congratulations.

10
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:31,200
Lara's pregnant?

11
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:32,367
Congrats!

12
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:34,067
Godmother, I think this bank
is about to be robbed.

13
00:00:34,233 --> 00:00:36,433
Don't go playing the hero,
Bobby.

14
00:00:38,767 --> 00:00:40,667
Nobody here has to get hurt!

15
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:44,733
We just need the money!

16
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:47,900
Where's the vault?

17
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:56,700
Where's the vault?

18
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:57,900
Right here.

19
00:00:58,033 --> 00:01:00,200
Come, come here!

20
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:02,200
- Give it to me.
- Here.

21
00:01:05,933 --> 00:01:07,000
Vault...

22
00:01:07,167 --> 00:01:08,400
Vault, vault, vault...

23
00:01:08,533 --> 00:01:10,667
Where are you, vault?

24
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:12,000
Vault...

25
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:24,500
- Get up! Get up!
- Hey, get up!

26
00:01:24,633 --> 00:01:25,800
Put your hands up!

27
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,533
Where's the vault?

28
00:01:36,933 --> 00:01:38,533
- Get it!
- Where is it?

29
00:01:38,667 --> 00:01:40,500
I'll take care of this.

30
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:46,600
Hurry!

31
00:02:07,133 --> 00:02:08,633
Stop!

32
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:20,833
Put your hands up!

33
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,833
The guy I was talking to earlier
won't talk.

34
00:02:29,433 --> 00:02:30,967
I'll try the others
with him later.

35
00:02:31,100 --> 00:02:32,967
Maybe they'll sing better.

36
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:34,267
<i> Okay, Conde.</i>

37
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:38,433
When you get back, file your
leave so I can sign it.

38
00:02:38,967 --> 00:02:40,533
Okay, thank you.

39
00:03:12,533 --> 00:03:13,967
Lara...

40
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:19,000
I can't...

41
00:03:20,233 --> 00:03:22,833
I can't live without you.

42
00:03:25,133 --> 00:03:27,233
So please...

43
00:03:28,633 --> 00:03:30,867
please marry me.

44
00:04:10,367 --> 00:04:11,667
I need to go for a while.

45
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,467
Why? Where are you going?

46
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:15,367
I need to check on Bobby.

47
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:18,000
Something might've
happened to her.

48
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:20,800
Aren't you off duty?

49
00:04:23,033 --> 00:04:27,267
Love, a cop is never off duty.

50
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:30,400
I'll be quick. Promise.

51
00:04:35,300 --> 00:04:36,567
Oh, Mom...

52
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:37,767
You're going out?

53
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:39,700
I thought we were having lunch?

54
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:42,133
Dear, I'll just go out for a
bit.

55
00:04:42,267 --> 00:04:44,167
I'll just go to Bobby,

56
00:04:44,300 --> 00:04:46,533
but I'll be home soon.

57
00:04:47,167 --> 00:04:48,933
I'll go ahead.

58
00:04:49,367 --> 00:04:50,800
Mom!

59
00:04:58,767 --> 00:05:01,900
Miss, where's the pregnant
teller that was with you?

60
00:05:02,067 --> 00:05:04,733
I don't know
where she went either.

61
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,700
Hello?

62
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,800
I'll pick you up later, okay?

63
00:05:23,933 --> 00:05:25,767
It's still on, right?

64
00:05:33,133 --> 00:05:34,733
Hello?

65
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:39,733
Did you call the cops?

66
00:05:41,667 --> 00:05:42,900
You've got guts, huh?

67
00:05:43,033 --> 00:05:44,333
Fine!

68
00:05:44,467 --> 00:05:45,933
Down! Get down!

69
00:05:46,067 --> 00:05:47,700
Sit over there!

70
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,267
Oh...

71
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:58,433
My girl's moody again.

72
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:01,367
Oh, no worries.

73
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:04,533
Later, I'm sure that bad mood
will be gone.

74
00:06:08,933 --> 00:06:11,100
Oh...

75
00:06:20,067 --> 00:06:21,300
<i> All units, be advised.</i>

76
00:06:21,433 --> 00:06:23,667
<i>10-31 at Rural Bank
of San Isidro.</i>

77
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,733
<i> Robbery in progress.</i>

78
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:29,033
Lara...

79
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:54,933
That's enough!

80
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:28,600
Stop it, please!

81
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:38,733
What?

82
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:41,667
Give me the gun!

83
00:07:42,167 --> 00:07:45,900
Boss, I'll finish this!

84
00:07:53,667 --> 00:07:54,833
Get out of there now.

85
00:07:54,967 --> 00:07:56,600
The SWAT's coming.

86
00:08:03,933 --> 00:08:05,867
- That's enough!
- What?

87
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,700
The police are coming.

88
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,567
Let's go!

89
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,500
Come on.

90
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:22,633
Miss, come here.

91
00:08:24,233 --> 00:08:25,800
Miss, thank you.

92
00:08:25,933 --> 00:08:27,500
Thank you so much.

93
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:38,233
- Let's go! Let's go!
- Go!

94
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:41,200
Stop!

95
00:09:01,567 --> 00:09:03,100
The cops are here!
Go inside!

96
00:09:03,233 --> 00:09:05,033
Turn back, turn back!

97
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:10,433
How are you?

98
00:09:10,567 --> 00:09:11,633
Were you hurt?

99
00:09:11,767 --> 00:09:12,733
I'm okay.

100
00:09:12,867 --> 00:09:14,333
Your baby?

101
00:09:14,467 --> 00:09:15,900
We're okay.

102
00:09:17,367 --> 00:09:19,600
Thank you so much.

103
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:25,067
What's the status
at Lara's bank?

104
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,900
Station 11 is already there.

105
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:27,767
Where are you?

106
00:09:27,933 --> 00:09:29,600
One minute ETA, Sir.

107
00:09:29,733 --> 00:09:31,533
Conde, hurry.

108
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:32,900
Be careful.

109
00:09:41,067 --> 00:09:42,967
I'll help you.

110
00:09:49,533 --> 00:09:50,733
Get up.

111
00:09:50,867 --> 00:09:52,067
We have to escape.

112
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,733
Come on.

113
00:09:53,867 --> 00:09:56,000
Come on. Hurry.

114
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:04,400
- Hurry!
- You again?

115
00:10:04,967 --> 00:10:06,233
You're really stubborn, huh?

116
00:10:08,667 --> 00:10:10,033
That's enough!

117
00:10:10,167 --> 00:10:12,133
You, take care of the old folks.

118
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:17,867
I'll shoot you all! Get down!

119
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:28,933
Get down!

120
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,067
Stay right here.

121
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,867
Be careful.

122
00:10:44,367 --> 00:10:45,600
Go ahead!

123
00:10:45,733 --> 00:10:47,133
Try shooting!

124
00:10:47,267 --> 00:10:48,767
Don't make any mistake!

125
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:50,233
We will have
a killing-spree here!

126
00:10:50,367 --> 00:10:52,567
Come on, try me!

127
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,067
Lara!

128
00:11:17,333 --> 00:11:18,800
Bobby?

129
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:29,467
Godmother!

130
00:11:34,133 --> 00:11:36,167
Let's go, let's go,
let's go, let's go!

131
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:51,233
Godmother!

132
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:53,567
Bobby...

133
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,133
Godmother!

134
00:11:57,267 --> 00:11:58,233
Bobby, are you hurt?

135
00:11:58,367 --> 00:12:00,000
I'm not hurt, Godmother!

136
00:12:00,133 --> 00:12:01,300
Help!

137
00:12:01,433 --> 00:12:03,100
Someone help us!

138
00:12:03,233 --> 00:12:05,233
Someone help us!

139
00:12:05,367 --> 00:12:06,233
Hey!

140
00:12:06,367 --> 00:12:08,867
For mercy's sake, help us!

141
00:12:09,367 --> 00:12:11,833
Help! Hurry!

142
00:12:11,967 --> 00:12:13,367
Godmother!

143
00:12:14,033 --> 00:12:15,867
Godmother...

144
00:12:16,033 --> 00:12:18,200
Help! Hurry!

145
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:20,067
Quickly, quickly! Please hurry!

146
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,800
Quickly, quickly! Hurry!

147
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:46,900
Let me go!

148
00:12:47,033 --> 00:12:48,500
Let me go!

149
00:12:48,667 --> 00:12:50,100
Where are you taking me?

150
00:12:50,233 --> 00:12:51,800
Shut up!

151
00:12:58,400 --> 00:13:00,033
Lara!

152
00:13:03,167 --> 00:13:04,333
Boss, someone's following us.
On a motorcycle.

153
00:13:04,467 --> 00:13:05,633
What?

154
00:13:05,767 --> 00:13:07,067
That's right, Boss!

155
00:13:13,167 --> 00:13:15,600
It's a cop! Shoot him now!

156
00:13:15,733 --> 00:13:17,367
What are you waiting for?

157
00:13:20,033 --> 00:13:21,167
Move faster, hurry up!

158
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:23,067
His catching up on us!

159
00:13:32,967 --> 00:13:35,900
Please, let me go,
I'm begging you!

160
00:13:37,067 --> 00:13:39,000
What are you doing?
Aim properly!

161
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:49,600
Hey! Wake up!

162
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:52,933
Rain down bullets!
Make sure he's dead!

163
00:13:53,067 --> 00:13:54,867
- Yes, Boss!
- Hurry, hurry!

164
00:14:09,967 --> 00:14:12,967
Sir, permission
to take down safely, Sir!

165
00:14:13,967 --> 00:14:16,067
No, hold your fire!

166
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:18,233
There's a hostage
inside the van!

167
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,067
Lara!

168
00:14:25,567 --> 00:14:27,800
Hey, you...

169
00:14:28,433 --> 00:14:30,867
You know the one following us,
don't you?

170
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:33,767
Confess, or I'll blow
your brains out.

171
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:37,433
I'm pregnant.

172
00:14:37,567 --> 00:14:40,433
I don't care...

173
00:14:41,633 --> 00:14:44,333
Even if you're sick or pregnant!

174
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,633
You'll make it, Godmother...

175
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,533
We're almost at the hospital.

176
00:14:54,667 --> 00:14:56,200
Bobby...

177
00:14:56,667 --> 00:14:59,467
You take care of your godfather,
okay?

178
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,467
And to your godsibling.

179
00:15:01,633 --> 00:15:03,433
Don't talk like that, Godmother.

180
00:15:03,567 --> 00:15:04,767
You'll survive this.

181
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:07,967
And don't neglect yourself
either.

182
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:11,367
Your mom entrusted you to me.

183
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:12,967
Your grandmother
will get mad at me.

184
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:17,333
I'll be mad if you don't stop
saying that.

185
00:15:17,467 --> 00:15:18,333
Aren't we still supposed

186
00:15:18,467 --> 00:15:21,133
to celebrate your retirement,
Godmother?

187
00:15:21,733 --> 00:15:24,400
Live our dream, Bobby.

188
00:15:24,533 --> 00:15:26,667
Prove to them

189
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:29,367
that women like us

190
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:32,333
can be great investigators too.

191
00:15:33,067 --> 00:15:34,067
Yes, Godmother.

192
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:36,300
I promise.

193
00:15:36,467 --> 00:15:38,633
But you'll survive this,
Godmother.

194
00:15:38,767 --> 00:15:40,200
Mister!

195
00:15:40,333 --> 00:15:42,400
Mister, please hurry up!

196
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:46,467
Godmother...

197
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:48,067
Godmother!

198
00:15:48,567 --> 00:15:51,767
Godmother! Godmother!

199
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:53,733
Godmother!

200
00:15:55,267 --> 00:15:56,367
Godmother!

201
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:59,400
Godmother! Godmother!

202
00:15:59,533 --> 00:16:01,067
Godmother!

203
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:04,000
Godmother...
Godmother...

204
00:16:14,033 --> 00:16:15,833
What's wrong with you?
I'll do it!

205
00:16:15,967 --> 00:16:16,867
Oh!

206
00:16:25,767 --> 00:16:27,600
It's too fast!

207
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:33,233
There's a market over there.

208
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:34,433
Go through that.

209
00:16:34,567 --> 00:16:35,967
- Boss, what now?
- Doesn't matter.

210
00:16:36,100 --> 00:16:38,567
I know a way to escape.

211
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,567
Let's go!

212
00:17:07,833 --> 00:17:09,100
Fellow citizens!

213
00:17:09,233 --> 00:17:10,800
Receive your blessing!

214
00:17:13,767 --> 00:17:16,100
Merry Christmas!

215
00:17:18,333 --> 00:17:19,667
Lara!

216
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:22,600
Lara! Lara!

217
00:17:22,733 --> 00:17:24,067
Wow!

218
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:26,000
Enjoy!

219
00:17:30,633 --> 00:17:32,633
Lara! Lara!

220
00:17:32,767 --> 00:17:34,867
Help us, please, have mercy!

221
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,267
Let's bring her to the hospital!

222
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:38,000
I have a jeep,
let's load her there.

223
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,567
Here, here.

224
00:17:52,700 --> 00:17:54,333
Center, center.

225
00:18:02,633 --> 00:18:04,100
Mister, let's go!

226
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:16,767
You shouldn't have called
your godmother!

227
00:18:16,900 --> 00:18:20,300
You should've reported to me
or at least to the station!

228
00:18:20,533 --> 00:18:22,600
You know our chain of command!

229
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,433
You engaged with bank robbers

230
00:18:25,567 --> 00:18:28,167
even though you knew you were
outnumbered,

231
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:31,500
even though you knew
civilians could get hurt!

232
00:18:32,467 --> 00:18:35,767
You broke protocols,
Sergeant Enriquez!

233
00:18:37,767 --> 00:18:40,767
You disappoint me,
Sergeant Enriquez.

234
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:42,767
Not just me...

235
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:45,067
your Godmother Dina, too.

236
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:47,433
You let her down!

237
00:19:19,667 --> 00:19:21,600
Help us!

238
00:19:21,733 --> 00:19:23,367
Emergency! Please help us!

239
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:24,833
Doc!

240
00:19:24,967 --> 00:19:27,000
Emergency, please help!

241
00:19:28,633 --> 00:19:30,267
My wife...

242
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:32,767
please take care of my wife.

243
00:19:48,067 --> 00:19:50,733
Do everything you can
to save my wife, okay?

244
00:19:50,867 --> 00:19:52,267
Yes, Sir.

245
00:19:55,567 --> 00:19:57,200
Wife?

246
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:01,000
Lara...

247
00:20:02,333 --> 00:20:04,033
I heard that...

248
00:20:05,467 --> 00:20:06,833
Wife?

249
00:20:06,967 --> 00:20:08,300
Yes.

250
00:20:12,467 --> 00:20:14,300
Here, look.

251
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:20,767
We'll get married right after
you get out of here...

252
00:20:21,967 --> 00:20:24,367
for the sake of the child
we're going to have.

253
00:20:26,833 --> 00:20:28,467
Tonyo...

254
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:30,267
You know...

255
00:20:35,267 --> 00:20:39,400
I'm sorry if I ruined
your surprise.

256
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:44,267
Lara...

257
00:20:49,233 --> 00:20:51,133
Will you marry me?

258
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:54,133
Yes.

259
00:21:01,867 --> 00:21:03,100
- Sir, please stay here.
- Doc, Doc!

260
00:21:03,233 --> 00:21:04,567
What's happening?
What's happening?

261
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:06,500
What's going on
with the patient?

262
00:21:06,633 --> 00:21:08,133
It's seizure, Doc.

263
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:10,200
What's happening?

264
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:42,100
My grandchild!

265
00:21:42,267 --> 00:21:43,867
What happened?

266
00:21:44,667 --> 00:21:46,333
Are you hurt?

267
00:21:46,933 --> 00:21:48,367
Huh?

268
00:21:50,900 --> 00:21:53,667
Grandmother,
Godmother Dina is gone.

269
00:21:54,267 --> 00:21:56,433
She died because of me.

270
00:21:56,567 --> 00:21:58,100
What?

271
00:21:58,967 --> 00:22:02,267
- What?
- Grandmother...

272
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:05,100
Dear, just because they're
blaming you,

273
00:22:05,233 --> 00:22:07,167
doesn't mean it's your fault.

274
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:11,200
You didn't force her to go,
did you?

275
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:15,900
It was her decision.

276
00:22:16,067 --> 00:22:17,867
And why?

277
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,733
Were you the one who shot her?

278
00:22:19,867 --> 00:22:22,300
No, right?

279
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:24,567
But if I hadn't called
godmother,

280
00:22:24,700 --> 00:22:26,800
she wouldn't have gone
to the bank.

281
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:31,200
So I'm still the reason
why she's gone now.

282
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:35,767
Godmother's gone, Grandmother.

283
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:59,500
Conde!

284
00:23:00,733 --> 00:23:02,200
Sir...

285
00:23:03,233 --> 00:23:04,933
How's Lara?

286
00:23:05,833 --> 00:23:07,433
She's still in surgery, Sir.

287
00:23:09,467 --> 00:23:11,500
What happened to the robbers?

288
00:23:11,633 --> 00:23:13,900
Were they caught?

289
00:23:17,933 --> 00:23:19,533
How did that happen?

290
00:23:19,667 --> 00:23:22,400
The robbers threw money.

291
00:23:22,567 --> 00:23:23,533
It got chaotic on the street.

292
00:23:23,667 --> 00:23:25,167
People swarmed.

293
00:23:25,300 --> 00:23:26,767
The road got blocked
with traffic...

294
00:23:26,900 --> 00:23:28,300
and they got away.

295
00:23:32,433 --> 00:23:33,633
I just received a report...

296
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:37,500
that our brave police officer
passed away

297
00:23:37,967 --> 00:23:42,133
during the robbery
at the rural bank of San Isidro.

298
00:23:42,267 --> 00:23:45,800
Her name is
Sergeant Dina Manalo.

299
00:23:45,933 --> 00:23:47,800
She died a hero.

300
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,533
To you criminals out there...

301
00:23:51,533 --> 00:23:52,900
if you're watching this,

302
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,167
listen carefully.

303
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:58,500
She killed one of my people.

304
00:23:58,667 --> 00:24:02,167
Now, I swear to you...

305
00:24:03,367 --> 00:24:06,000
No matter where in the world you
hide,

306
00:24:07,133 --> 00:24:08,600
I will find you

307
00:24:08,733 --> 00:24:11,133
and bring you face to face

308
00:24:11,267 --> 00:24:14,200
with the justice you deserve!

309
00:24:15,033 --> 00:24:17,367
Soulless monsters like you...

310
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:20,667
I promise you will taste

311
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:22,767
the fist of El Hepe.

312
00:24:24,533 --> 00:24:26,900
My law will be the end of you!

313
00:24:27,433 --> 00:24:29,200
Oh, Sir...

314
00:24:29,367 --> 00:24:30,900
Excuse me.

315
00:24:32,233 --> 00:24:33,667
Doc...

316
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:36,000
How's my wife doing?

317
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:38,367
Well, actually, we're not
officially married yet...

318
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:41,633
but I think she accepted
my proposal earlier.

319
00:24:41,767 --> 00:24:43,733
Can I see her now?

320
00:24:43,867 --> 00:24:46,367
She dropped this earlier,
I just wanted to return it.

321
00:24:47,167 --> 00:24:48,233
I'm sorry, Sir...

322
00:24:48,367 --> 00:24:50,867
but your wife didn't make it.

323
00:24:51,433 --> 00:24:54,167
One of the veins in her brain
ruptured

324
00:24:54,300 --> 00:24:56,467
in a spot we couldn't reach.

325
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:58,833
We did everything
we could but...

326
00:24:58,967 --> 00:25:01,267
we really couldn't save her.

327
00:25:04,033 --> 00:25:05,200
I need to go see my wife.

328
00:25:06,833 --> 00:25:07,633
Conde!

329
00:25:07,767 --> 00:25:08,867
I will go to my wife!

330
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:10,967
I need my wife!

331
00:25:33,300 --> 00:25:35,933
Lara!

332
00:26:02,900 --> 00:26:04,433
I just received the news.

333
00:26:04,567 --> 00:26:06,900
I am not your relative,
to share my grief.

334
00:26:07,033 --> 00:26:08,800
She said she'd be gone
for just a short while

335
00:26:08,967 --> 00:26:09,967
because she was worried
about you!

336
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:12,133
It's your fault my wife is dead!

337
00:26:12,267 --> 00:26:13,333
Godfather, I'm sorry.

338
00:26:13,467 --> 00:26:14,900
It should've been you
who died instead!

339
00:26:15,033 --> 00:26:17,200
Get out! Don't ever come back
here again!

340
00:26:17,333 --> 00:26:18,467
Are you the one
handling the case?

341
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:19,533
That was Chief's order.

342
00:26:19,667 --> 00:26:21,500
I should be the one handling
this, not you.

343
00:26:21,633 --> 00:26:23,867
I won't let you take the law
into your own hands.

344
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,067
You're suspended!

345
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:27,867
Please give me those people
who killed my wife.

346
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,467
Hell's already waiting
for them anyway.

347
00:26:29,600 --> 00:26:31,133
Just like the robbers in the
movies...

348
00:26:31,267 --> 00:26:33,000
that's exactly what those
bank robbers were like.

349
00:26:33,133 --> 00:26:34,933
- Hey, come here.
- I don't want to go with you.

350
00:26:35,067 --> 00:26:37,267
Don't force the woman if she
doesn't want to go.

351
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:38,867
So cocky.
